{
  "texts": [
    "This symbiosis fosters a cohesive approach to academic excellence, where libraries directly influence the relevance and quality of educational programmes.",
    "The use of business intelligence for data-driven insights contributes to understanding the role of libraries in the academic ecosystem.",
    "For example, analysing peak service hours and user demographics can help refine staffing schedules or prioritise investment in digital resources that support learning (Khademizadeh et al., 2022).",
    "Additionally, BI enables libraries to generate evidence-based reports that display their contributions to student success and faculty productivity, strengthening their position as indispensable academic partners.",
    "For instance, BI empowers university libraries to analyse students' reading habits, enabling the development of personalised recommendations that promote engagement with diverse resources (Dogan et al., 2024)."
  ]
}